 <glossentry id="glos.formatter"><glossterm>FO Formatter</glossterm>
  <glossdef>
   <para>
    Renders the XSL-FO files created by the DocBook XSL stylesheets into various 
    output formats. The output format used most often is likely PDF. Other 
    formats that can usually be rendered into include:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Page description languages such as PDF, Postscript, and XPS.
      </para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Different raster and vector image formats such as PNG and SVG.
      </para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Text documents and web page documents such as TXT, RTF, and HTML.
      </para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Internal formats of the formatter.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
   <para>
    Well-known formatters include Apache FOP, XEP, and Antenna House Formatter. 
    Whereas the former is an open-source product, the latter two are proprietary 
    and paid solutions. Antenna House Formatter is incompatible with DAPS.
   </para>
  </glossdef>
 </glossentry>
