 <glossentry id="glos.svg"><glossterm>Scalable Vector Graphics</glossterm><acronym>SVG</acronym>
  <glossdef>
   <para>
    SVG is an XML-based vector graphics format which is supported by most modern 
    web browsers.
   </para>
   <para>
    Vector graphics formats are different from traditional raster graphics in 
    that they describe the exact shape of an object instead of using the lossy 
    process of subdividing an object into many individual raster points (such as 
    pixels). 
    </para>
  </glossdef>
 </glossentry>
